test_886,2,11,Sometimes these kids don't understand the danger they could be in! We have to keep tabs all the time
test_889,2,0,"I looked away for a minute, and the twins managed to find the magic markers and graffiti up the the living room wall during that time. Thank goodness the markers are washable. "
test_889,2,1,Oh no! That does show some creativity though! What did they draw?
test_889,2,2,"I feel like a bad parent for saying this, but I really have no idea! Dinosaurs, maybe? At least they didn't draw on each other this time."
test_889,2,3,"They draw on each other? haha. You're not a bad parent at all, maybe get them some paper and show them they can draw all over that instead"
test_889,2,4,"That's the funny thing. They've got so many supplies, but they seem to prefer everything else as a creative surface. Maybe they'll be famous some day and pay me back for all my labor :)"
test_889,2,5,Wouldn't that be amazing. I think it's great that you let them explore themselves like that. Are they old enough to be signed up for art classes?
test_889,2,6,"Yes and no. As you can see, they have some behavioral issues. Maybe a tutor would be better. I certainly can't help them with art, but maybe someone else can!"
test_889,2,7,"That's a great idea. You know what's best for them, and hey maybe the tutor can make it stick that they shouldn't draw on your walls anymore!"
test_889,2,8,"I would love that. I'm sure they'll grow out of it, and I'm looking forward to that day. By the way, tell me more about your houseboat! Is it as interesting as it sounds? Maybe I ought to get one in my retirement."
test_889,2,9,"It is very interesting to say the least. I'm still getting used to it, but I wanted to get out of my comfort zone and do something I would not usually do. Rocking on the water can be very soothing, but also terrifying because sometimes I worry if I'll sink!"
test_889,2,10,I'll bet! I think I'd have nightmares for sure. Is it dangerous?
test_889,2,11,"I did a ton of research and have insurance in case anything happens, so that calms me down a bit. If I have it in my mind that I'll be safe it stops me from panicking"
test_891,2,0,I just saw the best movie on netflix. I have got to tell you about it.
test_891,2,1,What movie did you see?
test_891,2,2,It's a documentary called The Social Dilemma. Have you seen it?
test_891,2,3,"Yes, I remember that movie. It was very thought-provoking, especially about the rewards our brain is receiving for interacting with social media."
test_891,2,4,"I don't use social media very much, but I made sure to talk to my kids about it. I don't want my grandchildren having their mental health affected!"
test_891,2,5,That's very wise of you to start that conversation with your children. What are you reading these days?
test_891,2,6,I am reading a cozy mystery series called Stranded in Provence. It is about an American who gets stuck in Provence during her vacation and starts solving crimes. What sort of things do you like to read?
test_891,2,7,I like to read memoirs. Right now I'm reading Born a Crime by Trevor Noah.
test_891,2,8,Born a Crime? That sounds interesting. Is Trevor Noah the man who took over for Jon Stewart?
test_891,2,9,"Yes, I think he's doing an excellent job on The Daily Show, and it's very interesting to read about how he grew up in apartheid South Africa."
test_891,2,10,I enjoy memoirs as well. I will have to check that out. I imagine he had a very interesting experience. What other memoirs do you recommend?
test_891,2,11,"I just finished reading I'm Still Here by Austin Channing Brown, which was also interesting and also related to racial issues. It's almost time for my run, so I will load up an audio book and head out."
test_892,2,0,What college do you plan to attend?
test_892,2,1,"I'm not really sure yet. I would love to go somewhere out of state, but I will probably have to go local to be able to afford it."
test_892,2,2,"I don't know. With those grades, you may be able to get scholarships to whatever school you want! Do you know what you want to study? That could help you pick a school if they have a good program for it"
test_892,2,3,Maybe. It's just so expensive. I think I want to be a nurse. It seems like it would be a good job and I like to help people.
test_892,2,4,That sounds like a fantastic career path! I bet there are some great programs in-state for that. Or you could go to community college for the first couple of years and save money! I kinda wish I had done that.
test_892,2,5,That is probably my smartest plan. What did you study for in college?
test_892,2,6,I studied philosophy. Probably why I ended up working on a farm. Too much to think about and ponder. I would rather be at peace with my animals in nature.  
test_892,2,7,That's interesting. I guess you have lots of time to ponder things when you're working on your farm... or do your kids make that difficult? 
test_892,2,8,"They are in school much of the day, so I have plenty of time think about the unknowable. It can weigh on you, ya know?"
test_892,2,9,"I guess so. I'm pretty busy with school and track, so not much time to ponder the unknown for me! Although being alone in nature sounds wonderful."
test_892,2,10,That is probably for the best at your age. No need to worry about all of that. How is track going? Do you plan to continue in college?
test_892,2,11,It's going great. I won hurdles in our last meet and my team came in first in the relay. I would love to continue track in college. That's one of the things I'm keeping in mind as I look for schools.
test_894,2,0,Where exactly are you? I am going to take a houseboat vacation and I thought your lake would be a good place for it.
test_894,2,1,I am actually on Puget Sound. You should definitely visit. There are so many beautiful places over here. I haven't even explored all of them. 
test_894,2,2,That would be wonderful! Do you have any recommendations for what to look for in a houseboat? I have never been in one and don't know what to look for in this vacation. Living on a houseboat must be amazing!
test_894,2,3,It is quite exciting! You can just stay with me! My houseboat is pretty spacious and I live by myself. When are you thinking of visiting? 
test_894,2,4,Oh wow thank you! I would love to travel in July or August. Maine gets pretty busy with vacationers in the summer and it would be nice to get away and be a vacationer myself. Do I need anything special for a trip to live on a houseboat?
test_894,2,5,"Not really but if I think of anything, I will let you know. Summer here is beautiful, you will love it! Are you helping your dad with the farm?"
test_894,2,6,"Yes, it is a lot of work! I enjoy it though. It has certainly brought me closer to my family- my dad and grandfather in particular. We work and bond and get to know each other more every day. What do you do for work?"
test_894,2,7,I opened a breakfast and coffee place by the shore. I like making people happy by feeding them. And I like listening to their life stories.
test_894,2,8,That sounds idyllic. How wonderful for you. It is amazing to do something you enjoy and I'm betting you learn something from your customers every day.
test_894,2,9,"Oh yes, I meet such interesting people. It was my dream to own a place like that.  What are you doing for work?"
test_894,2,10,I have an etsy shop and sell my handmade candles and other treats! I am doing something I enjoy and can work at my own pace while I tend to my family duties.
test_894,2,11,How fun! I need to check out your store. I love scented candles. How long have you been doing that?
test_897,2,0,"I got paid earlier for one of my pieces of work, so I decided to go out and buy some prosciutto.  You inspired me to think about collecting meat, too."
test_897,2,1,Oh man! Just be careful how you store it! I always try to eat my meat within 3-4 days. Then I find a new stash!
test_897,2,2,In that case maybe I'll buy only a little bit. Haha. What other meats would you recommend?
test_897,2,3,Venison is really good! Have you ever been hunting? My father was a great hunter!
test_897,2,4,"I've never tried hunting, but hunting big game, cleaning, and butchering it all myself is something I want to do in the future. Do you have any experience?"
test_897,2,5,Just a little! I don't have much time anymore because I am always working! How many hours a week do you spend at your profession?
